---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Accessories"
  description="Database, cache, and sidecar containers managed alongside your application"
  section="Configuration"
>
  <p>
    <em>Accessories</em> are long-running containers that Shuttle provisions and manages
    alongside your application services. They are typically stateful: databases, caches,
    search engines, mail catchers, and other infrastructure components.
  </p>
  <p>
    Unlike application services, accessories run the same container across deploys — they are
    not restarted when you deploy a new version of your app. Shuttle uses a SHA-256 hash of
    the accessory configuration to detect changes and reconcile only when the config changes.
  </p>

  <h2>Presets</h2>
  <p>
    Shuttle ships with opinionated presets for common accessories. A preset provides a
    sensible default image, volume mounts, and environment variable conventions.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Preset</th>
        <th>Default image</th>
        <th>Default port</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>postgres</code></td>
        <td><code>postgres:16-alpine</code></td>
        <td>5432</td>
        <td>PostgreSQL database server</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>mysql</code></td>
        <td><code>mysql:8.0</code></td>
        <td>3306</td>
        <td>MySQL database server</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>mariadb</code></td>
        <td><code>mariadb:11</code></td>
        <td>3306</td>
        <td>MariaDB database server</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>redis</code></td>
        <td><code>redis:7-alpine</code></td>
        <td>6379</td>
        <td>Redis in-memory data store</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>mailpit</code></td>
        <td><code>axllent/mailpit</code></td>
        <td>1025 / 8025</td>
        <td>SMTP mail catcher with web UI</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>meilisearch</code></td>
        <td><code>getmeili/meilisearch:latest</code></td>
        <td>7700</td>
        <td>Fast search engine</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Using a preset</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">accessories:
  postgres:
    preset: postgres
    env:
      POSTGRES_DB: my_app_production
      POSTGRES_USER: my_app
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: !secret DB_PASSWORD
  redis:
    preset: redis</code></pre>
  <p>
    The key (<code>postgres</code>, <code>redis</code>) is the container name on the server.
    Shuttle names the container <code>shuttle-&lt;app&gt;-&lt;key&gt;</code> to avoid collisions
    with other apps on the same host.
  </p>

  <h2>Overriding preset defaults</h2>
  <p>
    Any preset field can be overridden. Override the image version, add extra volumes, or
    change environment variables:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">accessories:
  postgres:
    preset: postgres
    image: postgres:15-alpine    # override the default postgres:16-alpine
    volumes:
      - /data/postgres:/var/lib/postgresql/data
    env:
      POSTGRES_DB: my_app_production
      POSTGRES_USER: my_app
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: !secret DB_PASSWORD</code></pre>

  <h2>Custom accessories</h2>
  <p>
    Use <code>image</code> instead of <code>preset</code> for accessories without a built-in
    preset:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">{`accessories:
  typesense:
    image: typesense/typesense:0.25.2
    port: 8108
    volumes:
      - /data/typesense:/data
    env:
      TYPESENSE_DATA_DIR: /data
      TYPESENSE_API_KEY: my-secret-key
    command: --data-dir=/data --api-key=my-secret-key`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Accessory fields</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Key</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>preset</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>Use a built-in preset. Mutually exclusive with <code>image</code>.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>image</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>Docker image to use. Mutually exclusive with <code>preset</code>.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>port</code></td>
        <td>number</td>
        <td>Host port to expose. The same port is mapped to the container.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>volumes</code></td>
        <td>string[]</td>
        <td>Volume mounts in <code>host:container</code> format.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>env</code></td>
        <td>map&lt;string, string&gt;</td>
        <td>Environment variables passed to the container. Use <code>!secret KEY</code> for encrypted values.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>command</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>Override the image's default command.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Idempotent reconciliation</h2>
  <p>
    Shuttle computes a SHA-256 hash of each accessory's full configuration (image, env, volumes,
    command). On every deploy, it compares the current hash against the running container's
    hash (stored in a label on the container).
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>If the hash matches, the accessory is left running unchanged.</li>
    <li>If the hash differs (e.g. you changed the image version or an env var), Shuttle stops
    the old container and starts a new one with the updated config.</li>
    <li>If the accessory does not exist yet, Shuttle creates it.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This means you can safely run <code>shuttle deploy</code> repeatedly without bouncing
    databases needlessly.
  </p>

  <h2>Full example</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">accessories:
  # Preset with overrides
  postgres:
    preset: postgres
    volumes:
      - /data/my-app/postgres:/var/lib/postgresql/data
    env:
      POSTGRES_DB: my_app_production
      POSTGRES_USER: my_app
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: !secret DB_PASSWORD

  # Simple preset, no overrides needed
  redis:
    preset: redis

  # Custom accessory — no preset available
  meilisearch:
    image: getmeili/meilisearch:v1.6
    port: 7700
    volumes:
      - /data/my-app/meilisearch:/meili_data
    env:
      MEILI_MASTER_KEY: !secret MEILI_MASTER_KEY

  # Mail catcher for staging environments
  mailpit:
    preset: mailpit</code></pre>

  <h2>Accessing accessories from your app</h2>
  <p>
    Accessories run on the same Docker network as your application containers. You can reach
    them by their container name:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Postgres: <code>shuttle-my-app-postgres:5432</code></li>
    <li>Redis: <code>shuttle-my-app-redis:6379</code></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For convenience, use the host <code>localhost</code> if your app containers use
    <code>network_mode: host</code>, or configure the host name as an environment variable:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">env:
  clear:
    DATABASE_URL: "postgres://my_app:@shuttle-my-app-postgres:5432/my_app_production"
    REDIS_URL: "redis://shuttle-my-app-redis:6379"</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
